So welcome to my channel!

This is a channel to show my work, going back to my College time right up to University final project and anything i do after that! You can really see the improvement of my work when you look through it all! 

But this is also my personal Youtube channel too, i post random things i shoot, small clips such as slow motion skate stuff right up to gigs i filmed on my phone or a small recording device, so there will be a real range of videos you will find. Media is a huge part of my life, i was in education studying media for 8 years, starting in high school.... and i don't see why i should seperate my personal stuff and my more "professional" stuff.

I also have a photography business by the name of Collision Photography, check out our Facebook Page - facebook.com/CPcollisionphotography 

So i hope you enjoy my videos, hit like and leave a comment if you do, i love feedback! Don't forget to hit subscribe either ;) Thanks guys!!

John is the Author of Make Money Online: Roadmap of a Dot Com Mogul, which rocketed to #1 on Amazon.com within the first week of release. He has written many other books and runs one of the biggest money making blogs in the world. He has been featured in such publications as The Vancouver Sun, the Globe and Mail, the New York Times, Entrepreneur Magazine, Ming Pao Magazine and BC Business Magazine. He has also appeared on numerous radio and television shows, like The Lab with Leo.

description:
Videos of me, my friends, and my family participating in slow motion videos and/or regular videos with a Panasonic - Lumix DMC-FZ150, Canon Rebel T3i w/assorted lens, and Go Pro Hero black edition +. The videos on this channel will range between many different genres including  silly comedy, nature orientated, slow motion activities, tutorials, and anything else I view as entertaining or something I would watch.
Concerning my upload frequency, I do not have nor will ever set a schedule for video uploads simply because I believe in quality over quantity and the fact that my future choices and actions are based largely on my education and career choice. Filming/editing will always remain as a hobby for me, something I could never pursue in the professional aspect. Whether or not I upload depends on a lot of factors like weather, free time, and most of all inspiration. While my video uploads are infrequent, as long as I have my cameras I will always try to make videos for others to see.

About the channel:

Welcome to my channel. 

This channel features Team Fortress 2 almost exclusively. Mostly featured here are guides, tutorials and other forms of infotainment. You will not find commentaries with face cam on this channel, but rather a complete scene switch instead. Here you will find my videos to be a bit slower paced than what is the norm, as that's what I make. You may find some videos who appear to be pure entertainment, but they are actually cleverly crafted to make you learn stuff without you even knowing. Think about that!

If you are new to the game and want to pick up some quick tips along the way that can help you become super good really fast (i mean like you will exceptionally good and like beat your friends who don't watch these videos).

Below are some links to various social media. I highly recommend my steamgroup as that is the best platform to interact with discussions, constructive feedback and such.
Check out my balance mod as well!

description:
G'day Trendsetters!, (Hello all)
                                                       Welcome to "Fishplate Films", and for those who don't know, a "Fishplate " is the term used for a rail joiner, mainly in the UK and Australia, and nothing to do with fish!!
     
This channel features rail fanning from down here in Australia and from my first tour of the United States and Canada ,plus construction of my BNSF, HO Scale model railroad , based loosely on Tehachapi and the mountains of Montana. You can see the construction from day one on the benchwork , up to present day, The layout is two levels with a double track Helix and has over 150 m of mainline, and traffic is based on grain, ethanol and Bio-Diesel.

Narrow gauge and Sugar Cane railways are also represented with many videos from my home State of Queensland. Thanks for stoping by and hope you enjoy the channel!

Cheers Gregg.

description:
TheLazyReader channel has one aim: doing our best to further the education of the Internet.

Currently we are producing a series called:
Easy Piano: Everything You Need to Know in 10 Videos

Our goal is to try our best to emulate the experience of being with a music teacher as best as possible.

To do that, we're trying an original approach. Instead of a single 20 minute videos, we're creating TEN 3 minute videos, each covering one concept. if you're having trouble grasping it, you can watch the video again (only 3 minutes long) and then try one of our many QUIZ videos. If you get the concept, feel free to just skip all of that and make your way to the next video.

UPDATE: Currently we have completed 3 out of the 10 videos in that series, which cover White Notes, Tones and Semi-Tones, and Black Notes. The next batch of videos should be out in the next two weeks. 

We're also planning on making Math and Science Tutorials, Minecraft Tutorials, and Audiobooks!

description:
Sri Ramakrishna Math, Chennai is a branch centre of Ramakrishna Math and Ramakrishna Mission, Belur Math, Howrah, West Bengal.
Math Activities:
1. Daily worship, Vedic chanting, Sandhya arati, Bhajans, Spiritual retreats, Festival celebrations, & Birthday celebrations of Sri Ramakrishna, Sri Sarada Devi, Swami Vivekananda & other avatars,
2. Publication of scriptural texts, books on Ramakrishna-Vivekananda teachings, Vedanta, Indian culture, and Self-improvement in Tamil and English languages,
3. Monthly Spiritual Magazines in English and Tamil,
4. Two Schools for economically backward students,
5. Yoga, Fine Arts, spoken Sanskrit/English/Hindi courses, Computer courses, and Personality Development courses at Vivekananda Cultural Centre,
6. Charitable Dispensary and Diagnostic centre utilised daily by over 700 poor patients,
7. Free Rural Medical Camps, 
8. Nursing Training for Rural girls, &
9. Rehabilitation of Leprosy Afflicted Persons
